Command Line Arguments

int main(int argc, char argv[])
input - echo hello, world
in c/c++ argc is 3
in java argc is 2

q1. given numbers as command line arguments print their sum	cmd_arg_sum.c

q2. diff between *++argv[0] and *(++argv[0])	  cmd_argv++.c

To convert char into desired data type
char *s = "15"
sscanf(s, "%d", &n)

you can also use atoi(), atof()

